item.description:
Example Let \(F(x)\) be defined for all real numbers except at \(x=0\) and \(x=1\), and satisfy the equation \(F(x) + F( \frac{x-1}{x}) = 1+x \). Find the function \(F(x)\)
Solution \begin{equation} \label{eq:1} F(x) + F(\frac{x-1}{x}) = 1+x \end{equation}
make \( x = \frac{x-1}{x} \), have
\begin{equation} \label{eq:2} F(\frac{x-1}{x}) +F(- \frac{1}{x-1}) = \frac{2x-1}{x} \end{equation}
make \( x = - \frac{1}{x-1} \) in \eqref{eq:2}, have
\begin{equation} \label{eq:3} F(- \frac{1}{x-1}) + F(x) = \frac{x-2}{x-1} \end{equation}
